  <div class="col-md-7">
    <p> So I got out the list of ships again and tried to get more information where the individual ships are during the fireworks. My favorite, the Emerald Star, should be too far away from the gift for my taste. I then looked for the Southern Cross. This ship was $ 100 more expensive, but the lady assured me on the phone that we stay close to the opera. So one of the best places for both fireworks should have. That sounded good and I decided to book it. </p>
    <p> On New Year's Eve myself, I worked for an hour or two in the morning before I made myself on my way to the investor much too early. Since I came to the closed port area without problems and without queuing, I now had a few hours until the ship came. Since there wasn't much going on at Sealife, I decided spontaneously. Thanks to my Merlin annual ticket, I no longer had to pay admission. </p>
    <p> After I wasted my too much planned time there, I slowly went to the ship. In the meantime, the weather had become even better and warmer. Each of the passengers was glad that cold drinks were available for greeting. And then the journey started. </p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-5 hidden-sm hidden-xs">
    <img class="img-bordered img-responsive img-center" src="{{ site.url }}/assets/img/blog/auszeit/small/20130202-153139.jpg" alt="Delicious fish in the Sealife Aquarium Darling Harbor">
