    <p> After the fireworks, I actually expected the many thousands of ships to make the alarm at least, but nothing was. Everyone just waited for the port to be released to make their way back. The ship on which I was did not put on the Darling Habrour again, but let us go between the opera and the bridge. So I then had a really tight walk in the middle of the closed George Street (main shopping street). Which was really surprising that even shops had even opened. Not only feed stalls but also hairdressers and clothes shops. Not many but anyway! Who will go shopping on January 1st in the morning at 2 a.m. Strange people here. </p>
